title._content: Closeup of Bright Red Sumac Leaves Growing in Johnson County Kansas near Kansas City...10/1974

description._content: Original Caption: Closeup of Bright Red Sumac Leaves Growing in Johnson County Kansas near Kansas City. It Is a Typical Plant of Tallgrass Prairie and Invades Areas of Grass That Are Not Maintained by Grazing Or Fire. Only Isolated Patches of Native Tallgrass Prairie Survive in the State after the Wave of Pioneers Plowed and Planted Crops in the Fertile Soil 10/1974 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-14716 Photographer: Duncan, Patricia D., 1932- Subjects: Johnson (Kansas, United States) county Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=557168 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
